# ClapClip - API & Database Specification (Phase 2)

This document specifies the SQLite database schema and backend HTTP API endpoints implemented for the YouTube integration, secure server-side credential management, and settings dashboard workflow.

---

## 💾 SQLite Database Schema

The SQLite database file `clipper.db` is stored in the root directory. Foreign keys are enabled (`PRAGMA foreign_keys = ON;`).

### 1. `channels` Table
Stores YouTube channel details, developer secrets, OAuth2 tokens, and status.

| Column | Type | Constraints | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `channel_id` | TEXT | PRIMARY KEY | Unique YouTube channel ID (e.g. `UC...`) |
| `channel_name` | TEXT | | Channel title |
| `channel_avatar` | TEXT | | URL to channel's default avatar thumbnail |
| `client_id` | TEXT | | Google OAuth 2.0 Web Client ID |
| `client_secret` | TEXT | | Google OAuth 2.0 Web Client Secret |
| `access_token` | TEXT | | Active Google API Access Token |
| `refresh_token` | TEXT | | Google API Refresh Token |
| `expires_at` | INTEGER | | Unix timestamp (ms) when the access token expires |
| `status` | TEXT | DEFAULT 'connected' | Health status (`connected`, `expired`, `needs_reauth`) |
| `created_at` | INTEGER | | Unix timestamp (ms) of creation |

### 2. `playlists` Table
Caches user playlists fetched from the YouTube Data API.

| Column | Type | Constraints | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `playlist_id` | TEXT | PRIMARY KEY | Unique YouTube playlist ID (e.g. `PL...`) |
| `channel_id` | TEXT | REFERENCES `channels`(`channel_id`) ON DELETE CASCADE | Associated YouTube channel ID |
| `title` | TEXT | | Title of the playlist |
| `synced_at` | INTEGER | | Unix timestamp (ms) when the playlist was cached |

### 3. `uploads` Table
Logs clip publication metrics and history statuses.

| Column | Type | Constraints | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `id` | INTEGER | PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT | Unique log ID |
| `video_id` | TEXT | | Source YouTube video ID (clipped video) |
| `title` | TEXT | | Uploaded clip title |
| `start_time` | REAL | | Clipper segment start boundary (seconds) |
| `end_time` | REAL | | Clipper segment end boundary (seconds) |
| `playlist_id` | TEXT | | Target playlist ID (null if uploaded to channel only) |
| `channel_id` | TEXT | REFERENCES `channels`(`channel_id`) ON DELETE CASCADE | Target YouTube channel ID |
| `status` | TEXT | DEFAULT 'pending' | Status (`pending`, `uploading`, `completed`, `failed`) |
| `error_message` | TEXT | | Stderr log or API error detail if status is `failed` |
| `youtube_video_id`| TEXT | | Generated YouTube video ID once uploaded |
| `created_at` | INTEGER | | Unix timestamp (ms) when the upload began |

